            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel align="right" bottom="false" left="true" ref="text_name" right="false" top="false" valign="middle" x="-7.0" y="29.0"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Blue 
Yonder 
SPM</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-E86E0408-F57D-4FBB-AACF-86AED368D92F" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Supply Allocation Report is reviewed based on customer segmentation/ prioritization logic</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-725E3AD6-9FB5-4631-8A28-C4D5CE9068C2" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>This step occurs only if product is place "on" allocation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-E6881734-E35A-47B5-8027-0499D58CB58B" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>There will be a manual escalation process (outside of nightly reprocessing) where a CBA can raise only critical orders (not everything) Scope of escalaltion file: Customer orders confirmed &amp; unconfirmed within the promise horizon Products on and off allocation Requires stronger justification than CMAD &gt;RMAD Excludes RTF and supply escalations (AR - Supply health escalations process TBD )</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-916643F6-F632-456A-AD95-D8C2ECDAE4FE" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Planners will be proactively reviewing Orders without CMAD / RDD vs CDD /Allocation and demand</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <group categoryValueRef="sid-6b8280b1-12e4-48ba-84f5-4c99e372be04" id="sid-CAFC35B9-3635-4281-9FD2-4C34ED0F2C0C">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
      </group>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-B7FD0341-EA0B-4479-B4D6-7D566AB87E1E" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text> This Master flow will represent O-030-030 / O-030-010 / O-030-020 / O-070-050</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-0911988E-BFC4-487B-ADF3-71349FCF0E40" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#99CC00"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#99cc00" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#99cc00" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Processes are happening outside of O-030-030 and are covered in subsequent L3s</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-E9F429CD-B4B7-4B0D-AEBB-98E3FDCE7884" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#FFCC00"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ffcc00" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ffcc00" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Processes are happening in BY</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-E7292F15-A3D6-41BB-B76E-7AD2BB0E5013" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower : OTC-Order To Cash
Process Group: O-Order Management
Process: O-030-030A Allocate Product to Orders (IP)</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-01B4C3B1-F992-4264-90F7-5B9C9BFEA474" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="true" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="36.0" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="true" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="36.0" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform Process Steward: Anita Sandhu &lt;anita.sandhu@intel.com&gt;, and BPM Champion: Rebeca, Meza Redondo &lt;rebeca.meza.redondo@intel.com&gt; of any changes that occur within the flow from now onwards so that changes can be accurately reflected within BIC</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
